<item>
            <title>[ENTESB-3833] Karaf history is overwritten, not added to, by administration clients</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-3833</link>
                <project id="12314570" key="ENTESB">JBoss Fuse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Karaf keeps a history of commands typed in its command-line console, whether entered locally or via a remote administration session. This history is stored in $HOME/.karaf/karaf.history.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If multiple administrations sessions are started, then the history file is updated only when the administration session ends. At that point, the file is overwritten completely with the history active in that session. Consequently, if multiple administration sessions are run, only the commands entered in one session are preserved in the history.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although the command history is intended to make the command line easier to use, some Fuse customers do use it as a simple way to record administrative actions for auditing purposes. That an administration session might be started and finished without any record being kept is inconvenient.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;JBoss Fuse 6.2 GA&lt;br/&gt;
JBoss Fuse 6.11&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
